post_text:
We understand that Athletics has become a hot topic on social media. Windsor Schools would like to clarify that our COVID situation has affected a large portion of our faculty. It is impossible for us to continue all of our sports for the next 14 days while considering the best interest of our coaches and athletes. We understand that sports are valuable and we will continue to monitor the situation.

In addition, we are communicating with Stew-Stras and will continue to do so as we work through this pandemic. We are unable to be consistent due to the differences of circumstances that we are facing. We appreciate your patience, Mr. Van Hoveln

post_text:
For High School students interested in participating in Golf this season:
- Practice begins Monday, August 10, at 9am at Timberlake Golf Course. The bus for those that need a ride will be leaving WHS at 8:40am and will return between 12 and 12:15 pm.
- Bring all equipment needed to golf.
- Golfers will need to make sure they have their face mask for practice.
- If you have not done so already, please contact Coach Forsythe at forsythej@windsorcusd.org if you intend on participating.
- If you are wanting to participate, but lack the equipment needed, do not let that discourage you. We have extra sets of clubs that athletes can use for the season.
- You can find information regarding the season schedule, player expectations, and parent/spectator expectations for the season on Coach Forsythe's school webpage by following this link https://sites.google.com/windsorcusd.org/forsythe/home/hatchets-golf
- If you have any questions or concerns, please contact Coach Forsythe at forsythej@windsorcusd.org.

post_text:
If you were unable to attend one of our two registration days last week, you may still register. If you have an elementary student, please register at the Elementary School. If you have a Jr/Sr High Student, please register at the Jr/Sr High. To register, you will need to call the respective building when you arrive and a staff member will meet you outside of the building. You will need to show proof of residency in two formats, such as a driver's license and a water bill. Next, a staff member will take your completed forms and ask you to remain outside or return to your car until registration is complete. Once the staff member has completed the registration process, they will alert you to registration fees. Please be prepared to pay these fees either with cash or check. If you missed our registration days, please get your student registered by Thursday, August 6 at 3 pm.

Elementary number: 459-2447
Jr/Sr. High number: 459-2636

post_text:
Last night, districts around the state received notification from State Superintendent Carmen Ayala stating “in-person graduation ceremonies of any kind are not allowed at this time. The directive extends to drive-through graduation ceremonies or events where students come in small groups to the school or another location for a photo or to walk across the stage. The Governor’s extended stay-at-home order prohibits group gatherings.”
We are extremely saddened to receive this newest directive but are working to find meaningful ways to celebrate our seniors and their great accomplishments.

The teachers and staff will have a parade through Windsor and Gays today beginning at 1 pm (in Windsor) and approximately 2 pm (in Gays). The route will begin at the elementary school and will mostly travel down the east and west roads through the towns. Please maintain social distancing (at least 6 feet apart from one another and no more than 10 people in an area) during parade. Candy will not be thrown at the parade, but you will be filled with plenty of waving teachers and staff.

post_text:
The following information was shared to us from Consolidated Communications:

We’d like to offer Free Internet Service to student households.

With so many students having to connect from home, our technology provider, Consolidated Communications, has offered two months of Free Home Internet Service to help, including free installation for those who are not currently Consolidated customers.
We agree that this is the responsible thing to do and we’re making this service available to our students immediately. Take advantage of this offer in two easy steps:

1. Call Consolidated Communications: 1-855-399-3084
2. Mention Offer Code: “Two Months Free”

Students who call may also take advantage of Consolidated’s current promotion on Internet service, so you can stay connected affordably even after the first two months. And Consolidated doesn’t cap the amount of data you can use or charge extra based on your use.

Smysor is here and open now until March 10th!

The Smysor Scholarship is now available through Southeastern Illinois Community Foundation. Students may access the application online at www.enrichingourcommunity.org/Student-Scholarships
They must first complete the Southeastern Illinois Community Foundation Common Scholarship Application to answer the financial, academic, and demographic information we require from all of our applicants. They will then complete the Smysor Scholarship application, which is only a few questions and specific to the scholarship

1/13/2020

Parents/Guardians:
Our 8th grade night for players and cheerleaders will be conducted at tomorrow evening’s home basketball game vs. Mattoon. The original plan was to have it on the 16th but our cheerleaders have a volleyball game that night at Teutopolis. We will recognize the players and cheerleaders along with their parents/guardians during halftime of the 7th grade game. We will introduce players and cheerleaders on the floor and will ask for parents/guardians to stand up in the bleachers when called.

Thank you,
Brian Lee
WSS Athletic Director
leeb@windsorcusd.org

post_text:
2019-2020 Windsor High School Homecoming Court
Windsor High School will be hosting its Homecoming Dance on Saturday, January 25th at the high school. Coronation will be at 7:30 and is open to the public. This year’s theme will be a Hawaiian Luau. Court members are pictured, Back Row L to R: King Candidates Mason Campbell, Brandon Milligan, and Eli Howard, Junior Attendant Morgan Greuel, Sophomore Attendant Sam Welton, and Freshman Attendant Rhett Rincker. Front Row L to R: Queen Candidates Ava Bennett, Hannah Reed, and Zoe Nichols, Junior Attendant Haley Beck, Sophomore Attendant Karlie Bean, and Freshman Attendant Kiersten Wheeler.

Happy 2020! We are excited to see the students back to school tomorrow (1/7)! As a reminder, absences should be called into the school office. Please select the absence mailbox and leave a message providing the student's name and reason for absence. Also, if your student is riding a different bus or a non-bus student needs to ride the bus, a note should be brought to the school office by 8 am.
The Elementary office can be reached at (217) 459-2447. The Jr/Sr. office can be reached at (217) 459-2636.

shared_text:
Regional Office of Education #11
November 27, 2019 at 1:48 PM ·

Regional Office of Education 11 is pleased to recognize State Senator Dale Righter with the ‘Friends of Education’ award.

Senator Righter serves the 55th district in the Illinois Senate. Senator Righter has regularly advocated for legislation that served the best interests of students and educators in our region and across the state, including recent legislative efforts to assist in reducing the teacher shortage. Always accessible and willing to listen, Senator Righter has visited Lerna Bridges, attended our annual legislative superintendent seminar, and met with us in his office at the capitol on multiple occasions. We appreciate his service to the students, school districts, and communities of our region. Thanks, Dale! #ROE11

Windsor FFA Chapter
December 9, 2019 at 8:35 AM ·

Windsor FFA took a team of 4 to the Greenhand Quiz Bowl last Thursday. While they were knocked out of the double elimination contest I’d have to say that they did a great job. They were studying all the way to Newton and knew most of the answers....those darned buzzers just weren’t activating quick enough on our side of the table. ☺️.

Nice job Sierra, Caiden, Joe & Rhett!!!
